FIVE people were killed when a mini bus and a truck collided on the R33 road near Doringfontein in Limpopo. The Toyota Dyna truck allegedly tried to overtake two motor vehicles and then collided head on with an oncoming VW Minibus. Following that the Dyna truck overturned. A 56-year-old driver of the truck and four passengers from the minibus - two males and two females were declared dead. The driver and four passengers from the mini bus sustained very serious injuries. Limpopo SAPS Nylstroom is investigating the cause of the accident. 